Exercise 04 — Format String Attack
=====================================

No overflow this time.
User input is passed directly to printf() without a format specifier.

When printf() sees %p or %x in your input, it reads values off the
stack. When it sees %n, it writes to memory.

A global variable 'secret' holds 0x4242.
You need to change it to 0x1337.

Your goal: overwrite secret using the format string vulnerability.
